Nyeri county is ready to host 30,000 people expected for this year&rsquo;s Madaraka Day celebrations at Kabiruini grounds next Thursday.Interior PS Karanja Kibicho said Kabiruini grounds have been rehabilitated to a national arena that will also benefit the county government in hosting other events. He spoke after inspecting the preparation work at the stadium on Wednesday. Kibicho was with a team drawn from different ministries, parastatals and county government dockets. Governor Samuel Wamathai said he is impressed with the progress.Kibicho said security will be beefed up during the celebrations. Wamathai urged Nyeri residents and those from neighbouring counties to turn out in numbers.President Uhuru Kenyatta is expected to preside over the national event. The preparations are jointly being done by the national and county governments.